The paper deals with face editing using a generative adversarial network, which is a popular technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of physically-based image formation and appropriate loss functions, which are common in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions the use of a disentangled latent representation, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
